message.raw:
separate print() and write() methods for the output box, one of which
obeys the semantics of thr python print() function (newlines, separators),
and the other of which is more like file.write(), with no newlines added
or anything.

Added colour, bold and italics options for text added with these methods
(or text received over the socket).

The old output(text, red=False) method is retained for backward compatibility.
